The Custom Software Development Process

Step 1
Requirement Gathering & Planning
We work closely with clients to understand their goals, target audience, and feature needs. During this stage, we define the project scope, set timelines, estimate costs, and document all requirements clearly.

Step 2
Design & Prototyping
In this phase, we design wireframes and UI/UX layouts, create a clickable prototype for client feedback, and finalize the technology stack.

Step 3
Development & Testing
We develop the frontend and backend based on the approved design, while simultaneously performing functional, usability, and security testing to ensure a reliable, bug-free product.

Step 4
Deployment & Maintenance
After testing and approval, the software is deployed live. We provide ongoing maintenance, updates, and improvements based on feedback and business needs.

FAQ

1. How do you approach custom software development projects?
We start with a discovery session to understand your business goals, users, and technical needs. Then we plan, design, develop, test, and deploy your software using agile methodology—ensuring continuous feedback and timely delivery.

2. How long does it take to build custom software?
It depends on the scope and complexity. A basic MVP may take 4–8 weeks, while a large enterprise solution could take 3–6 months. We provide a detailed timeline after the initial consultation and keep you updated throughout.

3. What technologies do you use for web and mobile development?
For web apps, we use frameworks like React, Vue, Django, and Node.js. For mobile apps, we offer native (Swift, Kotlin) and cross-platform (Flutter, React Native) solutions—based on what best fits your project.

4. Can you integrate third-party APIs or legacy systems?
Yes, we specialize in API development and integration. Whether it's payment gateways, CRMs, or legacy systems, we ensure secure and seamless communication between all your tools.

5. Do you provide post-launch maintenance and support?
Absolutely. We offer ongoing maintenance packages for bug fixes, performance monitoring, security updates, and feature enhancements to keep your software running smoothly.

6. Will I own the source code and IP of the software?
Yes. Once the project is completed and paid for, you get full ownership of the source code, intellectual property, and project documentation.

7. Can you scale the software as my business grows?
Yes, we build all custom software with scalability in mind. Whether you need to handle more users, add new features, or move to a cloud-native infrastructure—we ensure your system grows seamlessly with your business.

8. Do you sign NDAs to protect our idea and data?
Yes, confidentiality is a priority. We’re happy to sign a Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) before discussing your project, and we ensure all code, data, and documentation remain secure and private throughout the development process.

